{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"jdq1espvg8fvmtupqfrhdg1","title":"Text","desc":"","updated":1658539079620,"created":1658327154392,"custom":{},"fname":"reference.ui-design.text","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","name":"digital-garden","selfContained":true},"contentHash":"99fda33552d8a741fa487d8873638abc","links":[{"type":"ref","from":{"fname":"reference.ui-design.text","id":"jdq1espvg8fvmtupqfrhdg1","vaultName":"digital-garden"},"value":"reference.ui-design.fonts","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1,"offset":8},"end":{"line":3,"column":37,"offset":44},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"reference.ui-design.fonts"}},{"type":"ref","from":{"fname":"reference.ui-design.text","id":"jdq1espvg8fvmtupqfrhdg1","vaultName":"digital-garden"},"value":"reference.ui-design","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":3,"offset":905},"end":{"line":25,"column":40,"offset":942},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"reference.ui-design","anchorHeader":"alignment:#*"}},{"from":{"fname":"reference.ui-design","id":"8ibsbx74seaqalt8quejc2g","vaultName":"digital-garden"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":3,"offset":381},"end":{"line":14,"column":31,"offset":409},"indent":[]},"value":"reference.ui-design.text"}],"anchors":{"text":{"type":"header","text":"Text","value":"text","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"write-content-first":{"type":"header","text":"Write content first","value":"write-content-first","line":11,"column":0,"depth":2},"writing-copy":{"type":"header","text":"Writing copy","value":"writing-copy","line":17,"column":0,"depth":3},"line-length":{"type":"header","text":"Line length","value":"line-length","line":21,"column":0,"depth":2},"use-more-uppercase":{"type":"header","text":"Use more Uppercase","value":"use-more-uppercase","line":27,"column":0,"depth":2},"text-on-images":{"type":"header","text":"Text on Images","value":"text-on-images","line":35,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"8ibsbx74seaqalt8quejc2g","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"text\">Text<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#text\"></a></h1>\n<p></p><p></p><div class=\"portal-container\">\n<div class=\"portal-head\">\n<div class=\"portal-backlink\">\n<div class=\"portal-title\">From <span class=\"portal-text-title\">Fonts</span></div>\n<a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/x6hfk9zghtkqxd0925ugfrt\" class=\"portal-arrow\">Go to text <span class=\"right-arrow\">‚Üí</span></a>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"portal-parent-anchor\" class=\"portal-parent\" markdown=\"1\">\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-top\"></div>\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-bottom\"></div><h1 id=\"fonts\">Fonts<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#fonts\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-find-great-fonts\">How to find great fonts<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#how-to-find-great-fonts\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Check the fonts of great designs</li>\n<li>Have a collection of great fonts</li>\n<li><a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/5di5kvensezvok1cbaedws6\">Tools for Finding Font Pairings</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"some-recommendations\">Some Recommendations<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#some-recommendations\"></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Fira Sans: clean/simple with a side of warmth/humanity</li>\n<li>Inter: Un-opinionated and readable. If I found myself thinking ‚ÄúMan, I really want to use Helvetica here‚Äù,</li>\n<li>Clear Sans\n<ul>\n<li>squared-off feel, brands that are data-driven, scientific, masculine, or authoritative</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Source Sans Pro\n<ul>\n<li>neutral character, just a touch of humanist warmth, works great for user interfaces</li>\n<li>Has partner fonts: Source Serif, Source Code Pro (monospace) - but stands well on its own</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>PT Serif: more formal, knowledgeable, academic, official, or authoritative settings</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"size\">Size<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#size\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Not all font sizes work together well, use the calculator below to find sizes that work well together</li>\n<li><a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/40tilj5moa78uv2akteyhmz\">Tools for Finding Font Sizes</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"more-resources\">More resources<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#more-resources\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.designacademy.io/guesswork-typography\">DesignAcadamy - Taking the Guesswork out of Typography on the Web</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><p></p><p></p>\n<h2 id=\"write-content-first\">Write content first<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#write-content-first\"></a></h2>\n<p>Write all the content before designing anything. The design should support the content not constrain it to make it\nfit the design.</p>\n<p>Source: <a href=\"https://www.designacademy.io/content-first\">DesignAcademy - Why you need to write your content BEFORE you start designing ‚Äî and how to do it effectively</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"writing-copy\">Writing copy<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#writing-copy\"></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.designacademy.io/writing-copy-part-1\">https://www.designacademy.io/writing-copy-part-1</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.designacademy.io/writing-copy-part-2\">https://www.designacademy.io/writing-copy-part-2</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"line-length\">Line length<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#line-length\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>One line should be between 45-75 characters ideally.</li>\n<li>Adjust text column width to fit that</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> Design Academy - Debugging Design: Rejigging Layouts</p>\n<h2 id=\"use-more-uppercase\">Use more Uppercase<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#use-more-uppercase\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Feel free to use uppercase text in short text elements like menus, headlines, button labels</li>\n<li>It draws attention to those things</li>\n<li>It gives a bigger sense of alignment (i.e. that something was designed with intention)\n<p></p><div class=\"portal-container\">\n<div class=\"portal-head\">\n<div class=\"portal-backlink\">\n<div class=\"portal-title\">From <span class=\"portal-text-title\">UI Design</span></div>\n<a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/8ibsbx74seaqalt8quejc2g\" class=\"portal-arrow\">Go to text <span class=\"right-arrow\">‚Üí</span></a>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"portal-parent-anchor\" class=\"portal-parent\" markdown=\"1\">\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-top\"></div>\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-bottom\"></div><h2 id=\"alignment\">Alignment<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#alignment\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Design = Alignment</li>\n<li>You don't have to use a single line but still things are aligned to each other</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"/digital-garden/assets/images/alignment-example.png\" alt=\"Alignment example\"></p>\n</div></div><p></p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> Design Hacks - The easiest design tip (no one EVER teaches this ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è)</p>\n<h2 id=\"text-on-images\">Text on Images<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#text-on-images\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Text on images usually looks good!</li>\n<li>But if the image could be anything (like an user-uploaded profile picture), readability can be a problem</li>\n<li>Some solutions:\n<ul>\n<li>Use a dark box around the text</li>\n<li>Floor Fade - Use a black gradient on the bottom of the picture</li>\n<li>Tint the whole picture</li>\n<li>Text shadow (sometimes unreliable)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> Design Hacks - Why I‚Äôm jealous of graphic designers</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/8ibsbx74seaqalt8quejc2g\">UI Design</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"w4mxpqpj9ftyo6pw17k3wj6","title":"Home","desc":"","updated":1660372